Permission is hereby granted to individuals or organisations for the purpose of
academic research, teaching, or personal study to use, copy, modify, and distribute
this software and its associated documentation, subject to the following conditions:

1. Permitted Academic Use
   Academic use includes:
   - research conducted within universities or publicly funded research institutions
   - teaching and coursework
   - theses and dissertations
   - publication-related analysis
   - research funded by public or industry sources, provided that the results remain
     publicly disseminable and are not part of a commercial product or service

2. Prohibited Commercial Use
   This software may not be used, in whole or in part, for commercial purposes.
   Commercial purposes include, but are not limited to:
   - use by companies, consultancies, non-profit organisations, or government agencies
   - incorporation into proprietary products or services
   - use in commercial R&D or fee-based projects
   - use in industrial decision making, optimisation, planning, or operational processes
   - use in commercial training or commercial educational services

   Non-profit organisations are treated as commercial entities for the purposes of
   this licence and may not use the software without explicit permission.

3. Prohibited Use for AI Model Training
   The software, its outputs, structure, documentation, code, or data shall not be:
   - used to train machine learning models
   - incorporated into AI datasets
   - used for fine-tuning, embedding extraction, or feature harvesting
   - mined for model training corpora

4. Prohibited Military Use
   The software may not be used for:
   - military research or development
   - defence applications
   - weapons system modelling, optimisation, or planning
   - dual-use defence-related analysis

5. Modification
   Academic users are permitted to modify the software, provided that:
   - the modified version clearly states it has been modified
   - this licence is retained and applies to all modified versions
   - modified versions remain non-commercial

6. Redistribution
   Redistribution is permitted only for non-commercial academic purposes and only if:
   - this licence is included in full
   - attribution to the original authors is maintained

7. Citation Requirement
   Any academic use of this software, including modified versions, must include a
   citation to the following references:
	a. Hongyu Zhang, Ignacio E. Grossmann, Ken McKinnon, Brage Rugstad Knudsen, Rodrigo Garcia Nava, Asgeir Tomasgard,
	Integrated investment, retrofit and abandonment energy system planning with multi-timescale uncertainty using 
   stabilised adaptive Benders decomposition, European Journal of Operational Research, Volume 325, Issue 2, 2025, Pages 261-280, ISSN 0377-2217, 
   https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ejor.2025.04.005.
	b. Hongyu Zhang (2025). Richardzhang0416/REORIENT_Lite, https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17701723.

